The Kenya Medical Practitioners and Dentist Board-KMPDB has absolved neurosurgeons who operated on the wrong patient at the Kenyatta National Hospital from blame and pointed an accusing finger at the Ward Nurse Mary Nyambura Wahome. The board which spearhead investigations into the surgery mix-up saga attributed mishap to systemic failures at the hospital saying the 2 neurosurgeons who conducted the surgery Dr. Hudson Ng’ang’a and Dr. Mose Moraa were not at fault. This as Health Cabinet Secretary Sicily Kariuki said the suspension of Kenyatta National Hospital Chief Executive Lily Koros was procedural. 